 nowrap><b><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'>Briljin</font></b></td>
        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> Just out of curosity I would like to see what you guys would change about the possible PoP spells or what over spells you might add.  Here would be my list, mainly based upon the possible PoP spells.</P><P><b>61 Blood of Thule: 435 Mana 170DD + 1435DoT over 7 ticks 18 poison counters</b></P><P>Now I can kind of understand why they did not just give us Bane of Nife as an upgrade to Ebolt.  Considering Bane is a Kurnak era spell (which will be 3 expansion old) it would mean they would have to either add it to PoP drop tables or the issue of not being able to get it in current content would crop up.  Blood of Thule is actually very, very close to Bane of Nife in all aspects so it is not to bad.</P><P><b>65 Dark Plague: 375 Mana 100DD + 1800DoT over 20 ticks 18 disease counters</b></P><P>Just remove it, please.  No one using Disease based DoTs, not even Shamans.  They take way, way to long to deliver their damage and tend to carry a pretty high taunt factor.  Instead make this into an upgrade to Splurt.</P><P>Splurt upgrade: 350 mana, 2,500 damge over 15 ticks, Magic based with a -100 resistance check</P><P><b>63 Embracing Darkness: 425 Mana 73%-75% snare + 1845DoT over 15 ticks</b></P><P>Not sure how many Necromancers really use anything other then Dooming Darkness (I know that I use Dooming about 80% of the time), so another Darkness upgrade is really not all that exciting.  It takes 2.5 seconds longer to cast then Dooming but it also does not have Doomings 2.5 second recast timer either.  It has the highest snare rate of all known snares and it is actually a decent DoT (123 DPT with a 4.3 damage:mana ratio), maybe giving it a -100 resistance modifier would make it more appealing to Dooming users.</P><P><b>64 Touch of Death: 125 Mana 1000hp to Undead Target 500 damage to self</b></P><P>Do we really need a pet only heal?  I would change this into an upgrade to current Necro healing line (Shadowbond).</P><P>Touch of Death: 5 mana, transfers 250 HPs from the caster to the target each tick for 4 ticks (faster then our current Shadowbond line by 2 ticks).</P><P><b>63 Death’s Silence: 150 Mana Undead Mesmerize 30% mem blur lvl57 cap 5 tick duration</b></P><P>Really not a big fan of us getting better Mez abilities (really feel this is one area that Chanters should have as their own) but if nothing else I would change this into an upgrade to Screaming Terror and remove the Undead only target type.</P><P><b>64 Seduction of Saryn: 5 Mana 50 Mana per tick 63 damage per tick 205 tick duration</b></P><P>This is only about .2 more efficient then Master of Death but very few Necromancers will ever see that one anyways.  Even compared to Arch Lich it is only about .4 more efficient.  I would make it more efficent without increasing the mana regained (50 mana/tick is a nice jump from 35 mana/tick).</P><P>Seduction of Saryn: 5 mana, 50 mana per tick, 55 damage per tick (giving it a 1.1 rate) and please make sure this does not use some gimp ass model (IE Specter).</P><P>As for the pets.  <BR>* Warrior of Zek should be a tanking upgrade for EoT.  It should be able to take a serious beating and hold arggo (make /pet taunt mean something!).<BR>* Saryn’s Companion being a Rogue pet should be capable of high damage output when used correctly.  It should have high damage back stab (which it will use often) and the ability to evade to reduce it's taunt value.<BR>* Child of Bertoxxulous worries me.  While I like the idea of an SK pet I really hope VI thinks thru the spell selection this pet has.  It should not have ANY DoTs or Fear spells (PERIOD) but maybe some of the SKs self buffs, Life Taps, Damage Shields and a recyclable Harm Touch (if this thing is 51st level, that will hurt).</P><P>Some new spells I would add:</P><P>A upgrade to Funeral Pyre, now this one is a bit hard.  We would be hard pressed to get an upgrade that would match Blood of Saryn's 320 DPT rate because that would require an upgrade of over 700 damage (or 1/3rd of FPs current damage).  The problem is Blood is not just an upgrade to Bane but it an upgrade to Ancient Scourge.</P><P>I would be happy with a FP upgrade that does 2,700 damage over 9 ticks (300 DPT) for 525 mana (giving it a 5.1 ratio).  So it would do 20 DPT less then Blood but it would be more mana efficient, easier to land (remember FP is -100 resistance check upon test) and have a much lower taunt value.</P><P>A new Life Tap that has a bit of a twist upon the way we think of Life Taps.  Instead of them healing us for whatever damage they did, these would heal use for less but they would be higher in damage and mana efficiency.  A better cross over between Taps and DD for normal XP grouping.</P><P>Life Tap_001: 250 mana, 720 damage, heals Necromancer 360 HPs, 3 second casting time with no recast timer, magic based (-200 resistance check).</P><P>Life Tap_002: 330 mana, 1,000 damage, heals Necromancer 500 HPs, 4 second casting time with no recast timer, magic based (-200 resistance check).</P><P>A new spell in the Ward Undead line that does 1k damage for about 280 mana.</P><P>Add a upgrade to the Shackle line, that is a 70% slow.</P><P>Hmm... about all that I can think of right now.  So lets hear some of suggestions you may have.  We already know that the Devs do browse this board so lets try and give them some suggestions!</P><P>Bril</P><P><BR> </font></td>
