 things i do are: darkness fear pet ring, re-fear re-doom if needed). and i REALLY think velk ring is more easy to get (and far better stats) for a necro than a fungi for a SK (and it's even worse with the more and more fungi nerfs. on MT, the price is ATM 90k, still rising, what is it on your servers?)</P><P>so i did a compilation of what UPGRADES (no new spells or things like this, only spell upgrades) we DO need atm</P><P>*Lifetaps:<BR> An upgrade to Deflux, 2.5 (unfocusable) or 3.0 (focus to 2.5) casting time, bad ratio (exactly the same as deflux if they want), maybe a fun 666dd (already stated by another). could bother VI, but since we can already land 666 hits with some focused undeads DDs... (the 1st time i landed a 666 DD i felt fuckin'proud to be a necro ;) ), resist at least -300, maybe -400<BR> An upgrade to ToN: long casting (5.0 to 6.0), high damages (1k ish range), ratio a bit better than deflux 2, same kind of resists<BR> A real upgrade to VM, at least in the 1.5k ish range over 9 ticks, ratio a bit better then VM, or the same ratio<BR> An upgrade to the "godly" Zvefeer: group VM instead of group BoD for example, would for example be quite an upgrade</P><P>*Mana managing<BR> Maybe a lil upgrade to arch lich, but at least in the 0.7-0.8 range, less is NO effective upgrade, except in dps/rps, which is not necessary atm<BR> An upgrade to MW could also be cool, not necessary though</P><P>*Gifts<BR> A final upgrade of SB would be cool, maybe worsen a bit the ratio of the pet heal and make it all targets (like 750hp heal, 500hp drain, critable heal)</P><P>*DoTs<BR> A REAL upgrade to Dooming, the most commonly used darkness cause the only one with a bearable cast, at least in line with the SK one, maybe a bit better damages and/or dam/mana ratio (could be under our 49+ darknesses ratios though)<BR> An upgrade to the Pyre line, we need high damages, let's take them from where they already are, at least 3k ish fire low resist DoT<BR> An upgrade to Splurt, between 2.5 and 3k, with a slightly better ratio than splurt 1, same casting time, -100 ish resists at least<BR> A useable upgrade to the Asystole line: real melee debuffs (ATK/AC, hundreds of them), maybe a fuckin' high agro, at least in line with Slow ones, mid resists, the kind of spells you WANT for your guilds necros cause they could make some fights 20% less time (wouldn't that be godly?), but the spell a necro wouldn't often accept to cast W/O any problem (like "if you fail your FD once, you'll never get the chance to fail it one more time"), of course the mana cost would be crappy high so we couldn't use it soloing, it would be a raid/group spell<BR> Real poison/disease dots upgrades, even if not often useable, plague/ebolt can still be landed on some mobs and add some pretty dps. under shamen ones, of course, but please make'em better than what we should get, please</P><P>*Others<BR> An upgrade to PE, it sucks, we must get rid of it<BR> An upgrade to Invoke Fear, i already spent 20+ lvls with it, at 65 we'd use a 30lvls lower spell... we need to be able to charm high level mobs, we also need a few less resists on this fear, everything else (random duration included) would be exactly IF... of course it'd cost FAR more mana (like 2 times IF at least, maybe)<BR> A real upgrade to ST. make the new mez limited to 58-59 mobs, flagged all, 2.5-3.0 casting, same recast, still 5 ticks fixed duration, would allow us to mez up to 4 mobs (taking into account occasionnal resist and targetting time) in most situations, could be useful</P><P>That would ONLY be 60+ upgrades we DO need (i could have forgotten some, but i think it's not a bad list), didn't input pets/pets haste since we're gonna have upgrades, even if we don't know how they'll be (let's hope the rogue will 500ish BS, but i'm not sure it could even happen... sad)</P><P>What would also be cool (but more as a toy than as a really often useable spell):</P><P> A "raid purpose" darkness: the spell we now have in the 