 their melee.  being a caster, i would want a fast casting snare so i dont get melee'd to death.  since SKs tend to fear kite when solo, a long duration snare comes in handy.  since necros spend most of their lives fear kiting, a long duration snare is even more useful.</P><P>the design of this spell even suggests that it was intended for a necro.  who really benefits the most from fast casting?  a necro getting beat on, or a SK missing a couple of swings?  who typically has the best ratio dots?  who cannot afford to have a mob catch them when snare drops?  verant is obviously opposed to soloing, and truely this would make necros a little safer at soloing.  yet it also promotes SK soloing, so i dont see the logic here.</P><P>corpse summoning:</P><P>with SKs getting conjure corpse, i would like to see an upgrade.  a mana free summons OR a componentless summons would be a large improvement.  burning 700 mana AND a 70p coffin for each guild member in a wipeout is just a ridiculous timesink(dont point out right click robes, not every necro has one).  the corpse summon AA skill was a good start but useless unless they change the recast time.  since im on the topic i might as well point out that not being able to summon corpse across zones (but being able to rez across zones) and not being able to summon corpses of group members that are not in zone is a large hassle when it comes to summoning.  for a long time i have wanted a skill like ranger tracking for tracking corpses.  select the corpse you want to track, it autotargets, you summon the corpse.  if the corpse is not a group member or even if it is, pop up a confirmation box on that persons screen.  it would make summoning so much easier.  implement any of this in PoP and i would consider that a upgrade.</P><P>dot casting time:</P><P>this topic has been hinted at recently.  dots do not have the instantaneous dmg that a nuke does, yet they have long casting times.  the purpose of the cast time on a nuke is to limit the dps of the nuker.  long cast times do not belong on dots.  the only dots we have that would be an exception would be our snare line. the druid snare is 1.75 cast time, and new SK snare is 2.45 cast time so i wouldnt even expect to see anything over 3 secs on our snare line.</P><P>lifetaps and lifedots:</P><P>i dont know all the details here, but i have gotten the impression that the new SK lifetaps and lifedots have better efficiency or are faster casting than the necro spells (vex and deflux).  if this is true then the line has been crossed.</P><P>my recommendation:</P><P>make festering darkness useable by 63 SK / 39 NEC (scale dmg up with level)<BR>make 49+ darkness line fast casting and extend duration / dmg / ratio in accordance with festering darkness<BR>reduce casting times on dots<BR>do whatever needs to be done to necro lifetaps and lifedots so that they arent a joke compared to the new SK spells</P><P>Edited by - ameridian on 09/22/2002  13:30:04</font></td>
