        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> <BR>That's a good breakdown, Ameridian, even though I know what my necro did at level 49.  </P><P>I am glad you stuck with a soloing scenario, since in a group/raid setting the additional spells become irrelevant.</P><P>For an FYI, melee would add another 35 or so dps, for another 2100 damage per minute.  That's 4200 + 4400 = 8600 damage in 2 minutes.  </P><P>Two things I'd like to mention to improve the accuracy of your analysis:</P><P>1.  Blindfoe.  So many Arch Lich kills, so few SK's to loot them.  It's a sure bet that a level 62 SK will have Blindfoe (or the epic).  Blindfoe procs 3 ticks of Vexing Mordinia, which I believe doesn't stack with Bond of Death.  If this is the case, then Bond of Death will be useless for the majority of lvl 62 SK's out there.</P><P>2.  Combat damage.  I'll be taking it.  If I didn't want to take combat damage then I wouldn't be playing an SK.  I will be hard-pressed to say truthfully that an SK would be full health/mana after every fight with Lich.  Recent experience shows that I stay at around half-hp's and 1/3 mana with Kei's on.  It follows that with Lich instead of Kei's, I'll have more mana but less hp's.  </P><P>One last point...creatures that an SK would be soloing at level 62 are tougher than creatures that a necro would be soloing at level 49.  Thus the above problem would be compounded by the need to cast more taps, darks, etc., then the necro would to kill a given mob.  Not much of a factor, but a factor nonetheless.</P><P>I disagree that these spells are powerful upgrades.  They are good upgrades, no doubt, but not awe-inspiring.  For necros who rely on spells (and at a baser level, mana regeneration), they truly are excellent.  However, for an SK which relies on melee more than anything, they are simply more items for the utility belt.  </P><P>As it is, I think most SK's are still concerned about the loss of our aggro spells than any upcoming PoP spells (to put the loss of aggro spells into perspective:  Imagine your lich line of spells removed from the game...THAT would have as much of an effect on necro play as the loss of our aggro spells had on SK play).</P><P></P><P>In any case, wanting the proposed SK spells upgrades to disappear is not the way to go around getting better upgrades for the necro class.  </P><P></P><P><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=143036">Nodda Duma</a><BR>Grave Lord<BR><a href="http://www.catsinhats.net">Cats In Hats</a><BR>Drinal</font></td>
