        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> Ameridan, you are comparing us wrongly, you are thinking of what the spells in question do to mobs at level 49 not 65.  Level 60 exp mobs are 5000-8000 hp, expect level 65 exp mobs (atleast the PoP ones) to be in the 7-10k range.</P><P>With these spells, Ill take an average geared SK, at 65 with the pet and melee that should be about 75DPS assuming the mob doesnt have ungodly AC for some reason.</P><P>Fear kite:<BR>1. Go into lich<BR>2. Buff pet with augment dead<BR>3. Click be gloves for snare (engulfing darkness)<BR>4. Send in pet<BR>5. Fear mob<BR>6. Cast Shroud/Torrent of Hate<BR>7. Maintain darkness/fear until mob is dead.</P><P>Assuming 9k hp on the mob, it will take 120 seconds to kill the mob, with a mana cost of 420 (invoke fear x3... tap procs will handle the hp lost tanking for a few sec, and 120 for atk taps and pet buff), during the 120 seconds exactly 420 mana is regained through lich, leaving me right where I was when the kite started, meaning 2 minutes per mob.</P><P>Another breakdown of this fight if we cast more spells (just to show you how inefficent dots are for SK's), instead of BE gloves Festering Darkness is used which will give an extra 8.33 dps, bringing me to 83.33 dps.  The fight would then take 103 seconds, with a mana expendature of 520 (300 for 3 invoke fears, 100 for darkness, 120 for pet haste and ATK buffs) including mana regenerated from lich you regain 357 mana during the fight leaving you down 163 mana, which will take 5 ticks to regain, so 2 minutes 13 seconds per mob.  Not a huge difference but it adds up, espically when your well equipped and dish out more melee.</P><P>Toe to Toe:<BR>1. Make sure buffs are up (Cloak of the Akheva, shielding if you can, eyepatch if you can, damage shields, pet buff, etc)<BR>2. Pull with Asystole<BR>3. Send in pet<BR>4. Cast Shroud and Torrent of Hate<BR>5. Hit mob until its dead while maintaining debuffs.</P><P>Assuming the mob deals 30 dps (about the equilvaent of a 4500hp tank needing a ch every 2.5 minutes), DPS is increased by about 10 due to damage shields, and another 10 from Asystole, thus 95 DPS, the fight will last 95 seconds, requiring 420 mana for two asystoles, another 120 for shroud/torrent, about 20 for pet haste (broken down over time), so 560 mana spent, dps adjusted to approx 18 due to asystole/torrent/shroud, and another 7.5 taken off that due to shroud of death (assumes soul abrasion 3) so 11.5 dps taken, over 95 seconds that means the mob is able to hit you until fleeing (10%) so <BR>Pet only (few spots its doable, not many) 86 seconds of being hit thus 989 damage absorbed, 560 mana and 989 damage with an invigorate bp/lich will take 27 ticks to regain the mana (21/tick) with lich damage factored in you will get hp at a rate of 6.17/sec or about 37/tick, meaning 27 ticks to regain the hp as well, so 257 seconds per fight with downtime included, or 4 minutes 17 seconds</P><P>No Melee:<BR>1. Buff pet<BR>2. Pull with Cascading Darkness (will be festering in PoP) alternatively use be gloves<BR>3. Cast Invoke Fear, alternatively click be boots (exactly enough time to cast before your in melee range if using engulfing darkness)<BR>4. Cast other dots<BR>5. Med<BR>6. Repeat until dead</P><P>Only done this method a handful of times (sentient suits in WL when they were fearable and I was extremly bored) so my expierence with it is limited.  The pet should be about 28 DPS, 8.33 DPS on Festering, 13.33 on BoD, 10 on asystole,  8.33 on Ignite, for a grand total of 68 DPS at a mana cost of 79/tick (13.16/sec), assuming I can somehow mana to sit every single tick I will get 38/tick (6.33/sec) with lich up, at 68 dps thats 133 seconds/mob, I will lose 908 mana in that time, which will require 24 ticks to regain, so 277 seconds total for each mob this way, or 4 minutes 37 seconds per mob, this is hardly as efficent as you tried to make it sound.</P><P><BR> </font></td>
