o we put you back the way you were. <BR>UPDATE to the UPDATE: Druids complained louder than the other classes, so we gave you this stuff back, plus gave you a dot at level 1 that does 15K damage for 52 mana over 3 seconds. In the interest of fairness, it won't stack with any other classes' Dots. </P><P>Enchanters- We forgot about you, because you don't complain enough. <BR>UPDATE: The other classes complained, so we gave all your mez spells to the beastlords, but decided you can keep them, too. We felt this was a very logical move to make beastlords wanted at raids. </P><P>Magicians- Gave you a new spell: Summon Bubblegum. We are certain that the utter fun factor of this will ensure you a place on every raid and in every exp group, and as such, we took all your pets away. <BR>UPDATE: Due to magician complaints, we took away the Summon Bubblegum. And you can summon pets again, but all pet spells will drop off of level 60 or higher mobs. </P><P>Monks- We took the refresh timer off of FD to prevent any SKs or Necros from taking your place as the elite puller. We lowered the refresh time of Mend to 1 minute, and gave all Fungi tunics a +5 when worn by monks. Put bardsongs on all your equipment, bards aren't upset, though, because this managed to break all the bardsongs in the game, so they're too busy trying to get their songs fixed to notice that we gave them all away. <BR>UPDATE: Bard songs now work on monk gear, but not for bards. </P><P>Necros- We gave you a new dot at level 60 that does 11 damage per tick over 2 hours. We gave you the current SK AC and HP caps, because we upped theirs. We took away all your resists, though, in the interest of fairness. Necro armor with resists on it will no longer drop. <BR>UPDATE: Druids complained that your new dot is too powerful, so we lowered the damage to 3 damage per tick. Sorry for the inconvienence. </P><P>Paladins- We took the refresh time off of LOH. We are confident that clerics won't even notice this change as they will be too busy playing Gems. We also gave you the same AC as warriors, -5, and the same HP as warriors, -20. We gave you sow to make you more desired on raids. </P><P>Rangers- We gave you the ability to summon a horse because sow is too slow. From now on, you may only fire a bow from horseback, and you must be facing the mob to shoot it. Your horses will not run backwards, but you may sit backwards on them. You must be looking at the mob to fire the arrows, and you cannot steer the horse unless you are facing the same way as it. <BR>UPDATE: In the interest of keeping the game realistic, since you can't guide the horse, it will navigate on it's own. Unfortunately for you, your horses are insane from eating crazyweed, and will frequently head for cliffs, impale themselves on trees, and search for a large knot of red mobs. Increased bow crit aggro by 98%. </P><P>Rogues- All mobs will now see through sneak, none will see through hide. You can no longer sneak and hide at the same time. NOTE: If you complain, we will take away pickpocket. </P><P>Shadow Knights- Gave you all the necro spells except their new uber dot, and you get them 2 levels later. Raised your AC and HP to be equal to Paladins. We gave you duel weild and bash, but duel weild only works for sheilds. </P><P>Shaman- Gave you a 3,000 point heal at level 30. <BR>UPDATE: Clerics, Druids, and Paladins complained, so we took away your slows and you get the new heal at level 65. Be patient, PoP will come out in a few years, and while the new heal will still be bugged, at least you can still look forward to it working someday. </P><P>Warriors- Lowered your aggro factor by 55%, put all your weapons on the Emperor. We feel this will encourage more people to play warriors. <BR>UPDATE: The other tank classes complained that your weapons were too easy to get, so they will now drop off of the sleeper. Raised your aggro factor from 55% to 56%. </P><P>Wizards- Gave you group shadow step. It's useless, but we thought you'd get a laugh out of it. <BR>UPDATE: Took away your group shadow step because the other classes weren't inviting you to groups because of it. <BR>UPDATE to the UPDATE: We realized you couldn't get groups anyhow, so we gave group shadow step back, and made it work with targetgroupbuff. We are laughing our asses off over here!</P><P>Gnomb Goodbasher level 60 troll warrior Divine Legend - Terris Thule </P><P><BR><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=264137" target="_blank" target="_blank">Charbonez Soulmark</a><BR>Clan Doomit<BR>Duzzil Ro</font></td>
